  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points; the UQ campaign included one-at-a-time parameter sweeps and Latin-hypercube sampling to characterise output variance attributable to geometric tolerances and fluid viscosity. Results of that campaign are summarised in the validation evidence and inform the acceptance rationale, confirming robustness of the relative hemolysis index below the RH < 1 threshold.",
